Second Lady Karen Pence hosted a breakfast at the Vice President's Residence for attendees of the Creative Forces Clinical Research Summit. Mrs. Pence delivered welcome remarks and applauded the Creative Forces NEA Healing Arts Network for their work in understanding the impacts of creative arts therapies on patients with traumatic brain injury and post-traumatic stress. NEA Chairman Jane Chu expressed gratitude for Mrs. Pence's support of art therapy. The Research Summit aims to review clinical approaches to creative arts therapies and develop a five-year research agenda to measure their impact. The summit will take place on September 18-19 in Washington, D.C.